biography.text: One of dance music's first superstars, Detroit native MK (real name Marc Kinchen) is a record producer, DJ and remixer who's esteemed back catalogue boats over 2 billion global streams.  In 2013 his rework of 'Look Right Through' by Storm Queen hit #1 in the UK single chart, and was swiftly followed up with 'Pieces of Me', '17' and 'Back & Forth', singles that all went multi-platinum.  More recently, 2023 saw MK release 'Rhyme Dust' alongside Dom Dolla, a record that was nominated for 2 x ARIA awards in Australia and that quickly became one of the years biggest dance hits, as well as 'Asking' alongside Sonny Fodera, which peaked at #6 on the UK singles chart.
